The Berlin2CD pBridge now returns the same Micron READID bytes as the PIO
path. Exercise the page command and address path without attempting a full
page, ECC, OOB, randomizer, MTD, erase, or program implementation.

After identification has confirmed the exact 4 KiB/224-byte CS0 geometry,
read the first 32 bytes of page zero twice. Program the large-page NDCR
fields used by Valve and explicitly disable controller DMA, ECC, BCH, and
spare transfer. Issue a modern monolithic READ0/READSTART operation with a
one-MTU length override.

Require idle command, data, and completion semaphores before each pass.
Bound every wait, require CMDD and PAGED with no ECC status, pop the data
completion, require every pBridge engine to return idle, and restore the
identification-era controller registers only after that validation. Keep
the coherent buffers managed if a submitted descriptor becomes uncertain.

Reject an unchanged destination or mismatched repeated data. The operation
remains probe-only. Page zero is inside Valve's randomizer bypass region.
This test validates only raw command/address/data transport.

